Script Path - /opt/splunk/etc/apps/iPaaS/bin/iPaaS.py

 

Issue –

Whenever we have double codes(“) in the fulldescription field of the alert payload, the doublecodes(“) are being converted to %22 once the iPaaS script is executed. Hence, %22 reflecting in ServiceNow Description field instead of double codes(“).

 

Whenever we tried to send the Double code(“) as it then we have the Json parse error at API gateway of the Inthub. So, we tried to send the doublecode(“) with (\”) to avoid Json Parse errors. But somehow extra Backslash (\) is getting added. The result is (\\”). So again, getting Json parse error

 

 

Requirement:-

We want to send double codes(“)  to be reflected as it is in ServiceNow Description filed. so, required to send double code( ") with (\") to avoid Json parse errors.

 

Code:-

Total – 528 lines

Lines being used to process doublecodes(“) to %22 :-

Line Number - 46, escape_string function defined and this Function is being Utilized in Line number 283

 
